Hi @HarimbolaSantatra , we addressed this by adding Apache Archiva to the **repositories** section of the **buildscript**.  That is: 

`
    repositories {
        maven { url 'https://plugins.gradle.org/m2/' }
        mavenCentral()
        maven { url "https://archiva-repository.apache.org/archiva/repository/all-public/" }
    }
`

The above approach was adopted because we weren't sure that "io.github.rburgst:okhttp-digest:1.21" is an in-place replacement for "com.burgstaller:okhttp-digest:1.10".

@kulminsky Please make sure to follow the following format for PR title and commit message:
`FINERACT-XXXX: <short message>`

The ":" was missing from your actual title and commit message, but the above one is used to automatically pick up during a release and connect with the relevant jira ticket.
